A seal of approval
We are at the crossroad of the past and future. Tradition meets modernity. They act in synergy.
Inspired by Japanese
inkan
’s Cryptic Seals leverage groundbreaking blockchain technology to deliver
personalized graphical signatures to individuals who care about anonymity as much as transparency.
Each seal is a permanent non-fungible token stored on a distributed digital ledger: a perfect solution
due to its verifiable ownership combined with full traceability. But enough with the buzzwords: let’s be
honest here, who wouldn’t like to possess an official fucking seal of approval? From now on sign all
your electronic documents with your own seal. Would you like to show off a little? Why don't you
append it as a footnote to all of your emails? Or maybe your whole top secret organization needs an
exclusive symbol? Perhaps you would like to add a personal "watermark" to all your projects?
Now you can! Pretty cool, eh?
Your unique digital signature. On the Ethereum blockchain.
Blockchain revolution
Cryptic Seals are at the forefront of the next digital revolution: the blockchain technology.
Decentralised finance is just the beginning. How about a whole decentralised internet? Would you like
to secure your place in the world of tomorrow? Mark your support for the whole community with
a one-of-a-kind noteworthy symbol. Set it as your avatar wherever you log into: forums, social
media, marketplaces, messenger apps. Use the whole image or just place it in the corner of your
profile picture. Show everyone that you belong to the cryptoverse!
Aesthetic abstraction
It’s not only about utility. The beauty of Cryptic Seals lies in their simplicity and symmetry.
The collection is no less than contemporary art: the interplay of geometrical objects with abstract
concepts. Rigid in form, flexible in interpretation. Crafted according to concise math formulas. If these
are the qualities you value, maybe it is high time to own a unique piece of digital art? Let’s not stop
just there - how about you print it on a huge sheet of finest-quality paper, frame it and hang it in your
own living room or your office?
Perhaps your friends and co-workers will start recognising you as an art
connoisseur?
Take it to the next level!
